Example 1: Simulated Trial with a Single, Continuous Outcome - Final Analysis

Source: R/data.R
example_1_final.Rd

Simulated data from a randomized trial with four continuous outcomes obtained at 30, 60, 90, and 120 days post-randomization and continuous baseline covariates. This dataset contains the data observed by 1499 days since study initiation.

Usage

example_1_final

Format

example_1_final

A data frame with 239 rows and 15 columns:

.id

Participant ID

x_1, x_2, x_3, x_4

Baseline Covariates 1-4

tx

Binary treatment assignment (1 = Treatment; 0 = Control)

y_1, y_2, y_3, y_4

Outcomes at assessments 1-4

.enrollment_time

Time from study initiation to randomization

.t_1,.t_2,.t_3,.t_4

Study time of assessments 1-4
